C[Net (geta) — from Sensei's Library.
The basic form of a net. The marked White stone cannot escape:
If White plays a (ed), Black answers at b (fd); if White plays c (de), then d (df).]
AB[dc][ec][cd][be][ce]
AW[cb][ac][cc][bd][dd]
LB[ed:a][fd:b][de:c][df:d]
;B[ee]C[Correct! B1 — the net captures the marked stone.]
(;W[ed]C[White tries to escape via a.]
;B[fd]C[Black blocks at b — still caught.])
(;W[de]C[White tries to escape via c.]
;B[df]C[Black blocks at d — still caught.]))
